This paper is about an annotation tool for natural language processing tasks, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques for automatic labeling, which could be relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the customization of keybindings, which could be relevant to the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR) where keyboard shortcuts are often used for efficient searching. The paper also mentions the use of unicode support, which could be relevant to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) where natural language processing tasks often involve non-English languages. Finally, the paper discusses the user study comparing Slate with other tools, which could be relevant to the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) where user experience and usability are important factors.
